05/12/2008
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Floods caused by heavy rainfall left one person dead in southeastern Macedonia on Thursday (December 4th), media reported.
A 70-year-old woman drowned in her flooded basement apartment in the city of Radovis.
Authorities reported a man missing in the village of Dedino.
In other news, a large forest fire broke out on the Greek island of Rhodes late Wednesday, local and international media reported on Thursday.
Strong winds are hampering firefighting operations near Kameiros.
(AP, Makfax, MIA, MINA, A1, ANA-MPA, ERT, In.news - 04/12/08)
